-- Lehman Brokerage Trustee, Law Firm Seek $22.8 Million in Fees
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2010-12-02T22:54:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/lehman-brokerage-trustee-law-firm-seek-22-8-million-in-fees.html
The trustee of Lehman Brothers
Holdings Inc.’s defunct brokerage and his law firm are seeking
fees of $22.8 million for work done from Feb. 1 to May 31,
according to a court filing today.  James Giddens and his law firm, Hughes Hubbard & Reed LLP,
said they worked 49,743 hours, including 526 hours of Giddens’s
time, liquidating the remains of the brokerage. They are also
asking a judge to approve $403,978 in expenses.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
